parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause the brake pedal to feel mushy or soft, leading to loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when the engine is running. This can result in serious accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: rust or corrosion on fuel lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Pump Mounted Driver (PMD) can cause the diesel engine to stall unpredictably, leading to a loss of power steering and power-assisted braking. This can result in accidents, especially at high speeds.

The failure of the Engine Control Module (ECM) can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of power steering and braking, which can result in accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or navigating curves.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power during acceleration
vehicle stalls or dies while driving.
